{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":2},"link":"http://www.dotnetrocks.com/default.aspx?ShowNum=890","title":"Git Hub Greatness with Phil Haack","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1374120000000,"h":"2013-07-18T04:00:00.000Z"},"starred":false,"read":true,"content":"Carl and Richard talk to Phil Haack about his latest work at GitHub. The conversation starts out talking about semantic versioning, just trying to establish a coherent set of documents about how versioning should work. Phil then talks about licensing around GitHub, discussing a new service at GitHub to make it easier to select a software license - running down the differences between MIT, Apache and GPL licenses, and more! The discussion then digs into GitHub for Windows, or rather Phil's efforts to make GitHub generally more friendly for .NET developers. Lots of cool new features!","author":false,"_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":57}}
