{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":13},"link":"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Blogcoward/~3/V9nQ6734KrI/GlimpseNuGet-Doh-Reminder.aspx","title":"Glimpse/NuGet Doh Reminder","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1374537901000,"h":"2013-07-23T00:05:01.000Z"},"starred":false,"read":false,"content":"<p>So, I was looking at this<a href=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/IfYoureNotUsingGlimpseWithASPNETForDebuggingAndProfilingYoureMissingOut.aspx\">post</a>and liking all of the nifty functionality they’ve added to Glimpse (I’d checked it out a while ago, and not been that thrilled), and so installed the latest version.</p><p>Or so I thought.  When I ran my app, it kept telling me I had the previous version.  I uninstalled all packages and reinstalled, still nothing.  Naturally, I started cursing Nuget, as I am wont to do.</p><p>Oh, wait.  Hey, Johnny Dumbass Developer, if you add nuget packages, you think maybe you might want to recompile the app?</p><p>Oops.  Yeah, that will help.</p><img src=\"http://www.blogcoward.com/aggbug/929.aspx\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Blogcoward/~4/V9nQ6734KrI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>","author":"jdn","_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":130}}
