{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":54},"link":"http://thedailywtf.com/Articles/An-Exact-Measurement-of-Evil.aspx","title":"Error'd: An Exact Measurement of Evil","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1374229800000,"h":"2013-07-19T10:30:00.000Z"},"starred":false,"read":false,"content":"<p>\"The Sith in Star Wars the Old Republic really keep specific tabs on<u>exactly</u>how evil you are,\" writes<strong>Chris Osgood</strong>.</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-5\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-5.png\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><p>\"I was wondering why I never seemed to get update notifications for the AMD Catalyst drivers on my HTPC,\" wrote<strong>Erik T.</strong>, \"It turns out the auto update service is just really, really good at procrastination.\"</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-1\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-1.png\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><p>\"Citi is so security conscious that they even protect my own privacy from myself,\" wrote<strong>Max</strong>.</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-2\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-2.png\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><p>\"You know, this isn't<i>quite</i>what I had in mind when looking for lunch,\" writes<strong>Jason</strong>.</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-3\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-3.jpg\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><p><strong>Lucas C.</strong>remarked, \"I may not be a pilot, but I don't think that this is the shortest route to Washington Dulles Airport.\"</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-4\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-4.jpg\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><p><strong>Pat</strong>wrote, \"I wasn't looking for a new camera, but at that price...\"</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-6\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-6.png\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><p>Either<strong>Thomas</strong>caught a picture of some \"unlicensed advertising\" in Copenhagen...or it's a clever ad for LiveConnect.</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"#Pic-7\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://img.thedailywtf.com/images/13/q3/e74/Pic-7.jpg\" /></a></p><p> </p></blockquote><div style=\"margin:10px;padding:5px;background-color:#eee;\"><div style=\"min-height:45px\"><img src=\"http://thedailywtf.com/tizes/ads/inedo40x40.png\" style=\"display:block;float:left;margin-right:4px;\">[Advertisement]<b>Make your team a DevOps team with<a href=\"http://inedo.com/?utm_source=tdwtf&utm_medium=afooter&utm_campaign=tdwtf13q1\">BuildMaster</a></b>. Pairing an easy-to-use web UI with a free base platform, BuildMaster gets you started in minutes. See how<a href=\"http://inedo.com/buildmaster/case-studies?utm_source=tdwtf&utm_medium=afooter&utm_campaign=tdwtf13q1\">Allrecipes.com and others</a>use BuildMaster to automate their software delivery.</div></div><div style=\"clear:both;\"></div><div class=\"feedflare\"><a href=\"http://syndication.thedailywtf.com/~ff/TheDailyWtf?a=Go5uNI4rSbQ:LX3caYrBs28:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/TheDailyWtf?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a></div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/TheDailyWtf/~4/Go5uNI4rSbQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>","author":"Mark Bowytz","_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":217}}
