{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":44},"link":"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TroyHunt/~3/__5EgUbkdhQ/of-developers-security-professionals.html","title":"Of developers, security professionals and playing nice together on PaulDotCom","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1374618180001,"h":"2013-07-23T22:23:00.001Z"},"starred":false,"read":false,"content":"<p>Last week I had a video chat with the guys over on<a href=\"http://pauldotcom.com/\">PaulDotCom</a>(which, of course is at<a href=\"http://pauldotcom.com/\">pauldotcom.com</a>) on a whole bunch of app sec related issues, specifically around how developers can become more security aware. We also spoke quite a bit on how developers and security people can generally get along with each other better than what they tend to at present which IMHO, is often a rather corrosive current state of affairs.</p><p>There’s a bit of banter in the introduction so if you just want to skip direct to the interview, jump over to about 12:30.</p><iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"480\" src=\"http://blip.tv/players/xplayer?id=6618248&autoplay=false&onsite=true&no_postroll=true\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/TroyHunt/~4/__5EgUbkdhQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>","author":"Troy Hunt","_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":401}}
