{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":2},"link":"http://www.dotnetrocks.com/default.aspx?ShowNum=889","title":"Silverlight Skills on the Web with Dan Wahlin","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1373947200000,"h":"2013-07-16T04:00:00.000Z"},"starred":false,"read":false,"content":"Carl and Richard talk to Dan Wahlin about his experiences building web pages from a Silverlight perspective. The conversation starts out talking about how XAML isn't going away - there's lots of WPF development going on out there today. And Silverlight too! Microsoft has finally published some guidance around all of these technologies, check the links for the white paper. Dan also digs into how skills and expectations like data binding from technologies like Silverlight have changed web development - just look at the proliferation of libraries!","author":false,"_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":451}}
