{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":43},"link":"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ReflectivePerspective/~3/QmvlntVqn-8/","title":"The Morning Brew #1411","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1375345930000,"h":"2013-08-01T08:32:10.000Z"},"starred":false,"read":true,"content":"<h3>Software</h3><ul><li><a href=\"http://weblogs.asp.net/scottgu/archive/2013/07/31/announcing-the-release-of-the-windows-azure-sdk-2-1-for-net.aspx\">Announcing the release of the Windows Azure SDK 2.1 for .NET</a> - Scott Guthrie announces the release of the Windows Azure SDK 2.1 for .NET which brings Visual Studio 2013 Preview support, including server management via Server Explorer, along with tooling improvements for many of the Azure services</li><li><a href=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/b/bharry/archive/2013/07/31/the-improved-microsoft-developer-network.aspx\">The Improved Microsoft Developer Network</a> - Brian Harry announces the launch of the new and improved MSDN website with a focus on their key aims of  being simple, relevant and community driven</li></ul><h3>Information</h3><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.strathweb.com/2013/07/owin-middleware-asp-net-web-api-and-clients-ip-address/\">Owin middleware, ASP.NET Web API and client’s IP address</a> - Fillip W takes a look at retrieving che client IP address in Web API through the OWIN interfaces</li><li><a href=\"http://www.cloudidentity.com/blog/2013/07/30/securing-a-web-api-with-windows-server-2012-r2-adfs-and-katana/\">Securing a Web API with Windows Server 2012 R2 ADFS and Katana</a> - Vittorio Bertocci takes a look at implementing Active Directory authentication for your ASP.NET MVC web applications when running on Katana.</li><li><a href=\"http://devhammer.net/webgl-hello-world-in-ie11\">WebGL Hello World in IE11</a> - Devhammer highlights the inclusion of WebGL in Internet Explorer 11 and takes a look at using it with some simple samples.</li><li><a href=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ie/archive/2013/07/31/ie11-touch-browsing-for-today-s-web-and-beyond.aspx\">IE11: Touch Browsing for Today’s Web and Beyond</a> - Michael Patten of the Internet Explorer team discusses the improvements to various aspects of the Touch support in Internet Explorer 11</li><li><a href=\"http://www.devcurry.com/2013/07/aspnet-web-api-20-and-new-odata-keywords.html#.UfoPCG10qwX\">ASP.NET Web API 2.0 and the new OData keywords</a> - Suprotim Agarwal takes a look at the improved OData support included in ASP.NET Web API 2.0 walking through an example which demonstrates the new keywords</li><li><a href=\"http://www.codeproject.com/Tips/629658/Introduction-to-Qunit\">Introduction to Qunit</a> -  Carlos Luis gives a short introduction to writing unit tests for JavaScript based code using QUnit in this CodeProject article.</li></ul><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ReflectivePerspective/~4/QmvlntVqn-8\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>","author":"Chris Alcock","_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":1948}}
