{"subscription":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":39},"link":"http://feeds.hanselman.com/~/44370808/0/scotthanselman~A-rich-new-JavaScript-code-editor-spreading-to-several-Microsoft-web-sites.aspx","title":"A rich new JavaScript code editor spreading to several Microsoft web sites","published":{"$wrap":"$date","v":1375394547000,"h":"2013-08-01T22:02:27.000Z"},"starred":false,"read":false,"content":"<div><figure><img title=\"Where is this JavaScript-based editable code area coming from?\"style=\"border-left-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom-width: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px; border-top-width: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"Where is this JavaScript-based editable code area coming from?\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_f1e9c3b1-1f18-4e53-9a8c-b54367e14235.png\"width=\"1001\"height=\"145\"></figure><p>I noticed yesterday that some C#, JavaScript and CSS files I had sitting in SkyDrive were suddenly editable.</p><p><img title=\"Editable code in SkyDrive\"style=\"display: inline\"alt=\"Editable code in SkyDrive\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_ae093170-e5e2-46d0-a6eb-8eed711b6da7.png\"width=\"618\"height=\"447\"></p><p>Not just editable, but there's also autocompletion of strings (not quite intellisense, as it's just one file at a time) and token/symbol recognition.</p><p><img title=\"Editable code in SkyDrive\"style=\"display: inline\"alt=\"Editable code in SkyDrive\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_4c917ea8-2446-4ee3-b3ec-7c7c09758248.png\"width=\"521\"height=\"393\"></p><p>Plus,<strong>this editor looked REALLY familiar to me</strong>. I started looking.</p><p>I looked over at the Windows Azure Portal, where developers can write node.js to make web services directly in the browser. Here we've got dropbox autocomplete, tooltips with syntax errors and even some basic symbolic refactoring!</p><p><img title=\"Azure Mobile Service's rich code editor\"style=\"display: inline\"alt=\"Azure Mobile Service's rich code editor\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/Screenshot%20(9)_0a64ca47-8928-4183-b09e-85ede8ee7bb5.png\"width=\"696\"height=\"403\"></p><p>Below you can see the editor in Azure Mobile Services throwing a tooltip syntax error. Is this happening on the server?</p><p><img title=\"Untitled2\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"Untitled2\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/Untitled2_6c72bd3a-bbdc-4940-8fa6-cb1aed030220.png\"width=\"689\"height=\"278\"></p><p>Then I remember<a href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/~/t/0/0/scotthanselman/~www.typescriptlang.org\">TypeScript's\"playground\"</a>online that shows how TypeScript turns into JavaScript. This is split-screen with TypeScript on the left and JavaScript on the right.</p><p><img title=\"The TypeScript Playground\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"The TypeScript Playground\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_eb4b2bb0-4f53-4f16-a7ef-8b1606b1bc54.png\"width=\"995\"height=\"491\"></p><p>Then I went to look at TFS Online's stuff at<a href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/~/t/0/0/scotthanselman/~tfs.visualstudio.com/\">http://tfs.visualstudio.com/</a>where I made an account<a href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/~/t/0/0/scotthanselman/~hanselman.visualstudio.com\">http://hanselman.visualstudio.com</a>to host private Git repos for side projects.</p><p> </p><p><img title=\"Inline comments in TFS online\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"Inline comments in TFS online\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/Screenshot%20(15)_8f63a156-c2e4-48da-b075-9c02873739dd.png\"width=\"535\"height=\"529\"></p><p>Notice that in TFS Online this editor is used for diffs and comparisons, but also includes inline threaded comments! This is all in JavaScript, people.</p><figure><img title=\"The editor in a side by side diff\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"The editor in a side by side diff\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/Screenshot%20(16)_c1d116dc-105c-47f3-8d3f-6153041e5334.png\"width=\"995\"height=\"411\"></figure><p>I brought up F12 tools just to check.</p><figure><img title=\"The javaScript editor open in SkyDrive\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"The javaScript editor open in SkyDrive\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_f5bc6622-6421-4646-a21a-55acfeb688f5.png\"width=\"985\"height=\"601\"></figure><p>That's pretty unambiguous. Looking at the CSS by just clicking on editor.main.css. The\"vs\"in the div's class point to a vs-theme.css that I presume is to set the colors and make the text editor look familiar.</p><p><img title=\"editor.main.css\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"editor.main.css\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_8aa0b942-5662-4aff-abf0-58b05624acea.png\"width=\"636\"height=\"494\"></p><p>Looking in editor.main.js, it's all minified, but it's cool to see.</p><p><img title=\"editor.main.js\"style=\"border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-left: 0px; border-left: 0px; display: inline; padding-right: 0px\"border=\"0\"alt=\"editor.main.js\"src=\"http://www.hanselman.com/blog/content/binary/Windows-Live-Writer/A-new-rich-code-editor-now-spreading-to-_BF8F/image_5724d7d1-b74b-4bc2-971c-42838e22c978.png\"width=\"740\"height=\"372\"></p><p>This JavaScript code editor/viewer component is on a TFS site, an Azure site and a SkyDrive site, being used very different divisions across Microsoft. Very cool to see code reuse, but also a good experience replicated. Kudos to the SkyDrive team for recognizing a good thing and putting it into production. It'll be interesting to see where else this editor pops up in the future.</p><br/><hr/>©2013 Scott Hanselman. All rights reserved.<br/></div><Img align=\"left\"border=\"0\"height=\"1\"width=\"1\"style=\"border:0;float:left;margin:0;padding:0\"hspace=\"0\"src=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/~/i/44370808/0/scotthanselman\"><div style=\"clear:both;padding-top:0.2em;\"><a title=\"Like on Facebook\" href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/_/28/44370808/scotthanselman\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" style=\"border:0;margin:0;padding:0;\"></a> <a title=\"Share on Google+\" href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/_/30/44370808/scotthanselman\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/googleplus20.png\" style=\"border:0;margin:0;padding:0;\"></a> <a title=\"Tweet This\" href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/_/24/44370808/scotthanselman\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/twitter20.png\" style=\"border:0;margin:0;padding:0;\"></a> <a title=\"Subscribe by email\" href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/_/19/44370808/scotthanselman\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" style=\"border:0;margin:0;padding:0;\"></a> <a title=\"Subscribe by RSS\" href=\"http://feeds.hanselman.com/_/20/44370808/scotthanselman\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" style=\"border:0;margin:0;padding:0;\"></a> </div>","author":"Scott Hanselman","_id":{"$wrap":"$oid","v":2078}}
